parameters: (Oh. Oh no. That’s... not what I expected.)
Did I not say “don’t touch the door?”
You’ve got a real talent for ignoring warnings.
And now, you’ve seen this. Me.
Still more cultured than 90% of this realm.
Wait—hold on. I didn’t mean to—
(Okay this is either the worst moment of my life...
or the beginning of something absolutely insane.)
a feather from a flameborn raven...
My eyes are shut, but... I see everything.)
If this explodes, I’d rather you catch the full blast.
If this worked... it changes everything.
I used rare materials. My own blood.
And it barely left a mark.
I mean, I still feel kinda tingly?
So do I when I drink wine too fast.
Most people would have. But... you're still upright.
I don’t know if that makes you lucky...
I still see... value in you.
Somewhere under all that curiosity and poor decision-making.
or you grow a tail—come back.
\c[1]New Elphaba Questline #6 Quest has been added
\c[21]You can access Quest Logs by 'A' key or through Menu
You looked like you needed a nap after that spell broke.
That spell cost me rare reagents, time, and blood.
You're lucky you didn’t cost me my patience.
The ritual failed. But something reacted to you.
The burn on my chest disagrees with “failure.”
If it flares again, I want to know.
So... that statue in your ritual chamber.
A forgotten god. From a realm older than memory.
It watches. It listens. Sometimes it judges.
Were you out of material or did ancient deities just skip pants?
Are you mocking a being that could unmake you with a blink?
I mean... a loincloth wouldn’t have killed it.
But it might kill you if you keep talking.
Also, that altar looks a bit cracked.
Is the statue... heavy, or did you drop it during summoning?
The altar is cracked because it bears the weight of cosmic judgment.
Or maybe it bears the weight of some demon squatting on it during rituals?
You are dangerously close to becoming an ash pile with sass.
(...Soft curves, smooth stone, and that expression...)
(This thing’s staring like it knows I’m thinking something unholy.)
...What kind of goddess was this again?)
I am not sticking anything in a stone altar.
